-- Wenzhou Official Removed Over Affair Exposed Online, Xinhua Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2013-04-02T13:48:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-02/wenzhou-official-removed-over-affair-exposed-online-xinhua-says.html
Wu Kaifeng, secretary-general of
Wenzhou in eastern  China ’s Zhejiang province, was removed from
his post after an alleged extramarital affair was exposed
online, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.  Wu, a member of the Standing Committee of Wenzhou’s
municipal Communist Party party committee, was punished for
violating party discipline, Xinhua said, citing the city’s
discipline department. The government will continue to
investigate, according to the report.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
